Vice President, Yemi Osinbajo is currently in his hometown, Ikenne, Ogun State for the on-going membership registration and revalidation exercise of the All Progressives Congress (APC). The vice president is expected to participate in the exercise today in his ward. Osinbajoâ€™s spokesman, Laolu Akande, disclosed this in a media advisory issued in Abuja. Osinbajo will be accompanied by Gov. Dapo Abiodun of Ogun and other party functionaries and members in the State. Recall that President Muhammadu Buhari also recently in Daura, Katsina State revalidated his APC membership status. The president participated in the exercise during his four days official visit to his hometown.